The Mayan calendar we're
talking about doesn't end.

00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:27.640 align:middle line:90%
That's all a fear game.

00:01:27.640 --> 00:01:29.180 align:middle line:90%
It's the cycle that ends.

00:01:29.180 --> 00:01:32.780 align:middle line:10%
INTERPRETER: I see no
scientific imperative for

00:01:32.780 --> 00:01:36.160 align:middle line:10%
nor do I have a personal
conviction that would support

00:01:36.160 --> 00:01:38.820 align:middle line:10%
the prophecy angle,
although I have

00:01:38.820 --> 00:01:41.833 align:middle line:10%
the highest regard for the
work of the Mayan astronomers.

00:01:41.833 --> 00:01:43.066 align:middle line:10%
THOMAS GORNITZ
(THROUGH INTERPRETER):

00:01:43.066 --> 00:01:46.235 align:middle line:10%
This sort of necessary shift
in consciousness doesn't just

00:01:46.235 --> 00:01:49.370 align:middle line:10%
somehow come about on its own.

00:01:49.370 --> 00:01:52.417 align:middle line:84%
It happens because we
work to achieve it.

00:01:52.417 --> 00:01:53.616 align:middle line:84%
DIETER BROERS
(THROUGH INTERPRETER):

00:01:53.616 --> 00:01:57.880 align:middle line:84%
I am convinced that a change
will come about in 2012.

00:01:57.880 --> 00:02:07.119 align:middle line:84%
But the question
is when is 2012?

00:02:07.119 --> 00:02:08.792 align:middle line:84%
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]
-Don't panic yet.

00:02:08.792 --> 00:02:13.175 align:middle line:90%
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:02:13.175 --> 00:02:14.640 align:middle line:90%


00:02:14.640 --> 00:02:16.270 align:middle line:84%
That's the date
that many doomsday

00:02:16.270 --> 00:02:22.234 align:middle line:84%
prophets are claiming the
world as we know it will end.

00:02:22.234 --> 00:02:26.707 align:middle line:90%
[ELECTRIC ZAPS]

00:02:26.707 --> 00:02:48.990 align:middle line:90%


00:02:48.990 --> 00:02:50.190 align:middle line:84%
MICHAEL KONIG
(THROUGH INTERPRETER):

00:02:50.190 --> 00:02:53.010 align:middle line:84%
I'm convinced that we're heading
towards a dramatic change

00:02:53.010 --> 00:02:55.260 align:middle line:90%
on this planet.

00:02:55.260 --> 00:02:57.570 align:middle line:84%
Everything we can
observe indicates this.

00:02:57.570 --> 00:03:01.050 align:middle line:84%
Climate change,
overpopulation, food shortages.

00:03:01.050 --> 00:03:05.110 align:middle line:84%
Everything is undergoing
an exponential development.

00:03:05.110 --> 00:03:07.670 align:middle line:84%
And we know that an
exponential function climbs

00:03:07.670 --> 00:03:09.880 align:middle line:84%
even higher until
the grade is so steep

00:03:09.880 --> 00:03:11.180 align:middle line:90%
that the system self-destructs.

00:03:11.180 --> 00:03:15.890 align:middle line:90%


00:03:15.890 --> 00:03:19.570 align:middle line:84%
RUPERT SHELDRAKE: The paradigm
shift that is already happening

00:03:19.570 --> 00:03:24.270 align:middle line:84%
first in physics-- biology
is lagging behind-- but it's

00:03:24.270 --> 00:03:24.990 align:middle line:90%
already happening.

00:03:24.990 --> 00:03:28.380 align:middle line:84%
It's a move towards a more
organic view of nature, a more

00:03:28.380 --> 00:03:30.440 align:middle line:90%
interconnected view of nature.

00:03:30.440 --> 00:03:32.505 align:middle line:84%
Where we see nature,
the whole universe,

00:03:32.505 --> 00:03:37.510 align:middle line:84%
the Earth, and living organisms
as organisms, not as machines.

00:03:37.510 --> 00:03:40.136 align:middle line:90%


00:03:40.136 --> 00:03:41.402 align:middle line:84%
ERNST SENKOWSKI
(THROUGH INTERPRETER):

00:03:41.402 --> 00:03:43.760 align:middle line:84%
We're abolishing
the word "explain."

00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:47.220 align:middle line:84%
Physicists have discovered
that nothing can be explained.

00:03:47.220 --> 00:03:50.260 align:middle line:84%
You can only describe something
within a certain framework.

00:03:50.260 --> 00:03:52.030 align:middle line:84%
Which leads you to
certain logical,

00:03:52.030 --> 00:03:55.420 align:middle line:84%
mathematical conclusions,
which are in turn interpreted.

00:03:55.420 --> 00:03:56.390 align:middle line:90%
And the battle is on.

00:03:56.390 --> 00:04:00.420 align:middle line:90%


00:04:00.420 --> 00:04:04.170 align:middle line:84%
GIULIANA CONFORTO: We are
developing our inner senses.

00:04:04.170 --> 00:04:06.858 align:middle line:90%
That is not [INAUDIBLE].

00:04:06.858 --> 00:04:09.170 align:middle line:90%
I don't know when.

00:04:09.170 --> 00:04:12.930 align:middle line:90%
Some people say 2012.

00:04:12.930 --> 00:04:13.695 align:middle line:90%
It might be.

00:04:13.695 --> 00:04:17.089 align:middle line:90%


00:04:17.089 --> 00:04:20.300 align:middle line:84%
FRANCINE BLAKE: My understanding
is that at that point

00:04:20.300 --> 00:04:23.320 align:middle line:90%
all possibilities will be open.

00:04:23.320 --> 00:04:24.630 align:middle line:90%
All possibilities.

00:04:24.630 --> 00:04:27.980 align:middle line:84%
To go down to hell forever or
to go up to heaven or whatever.

00:04:27.980 --> 00:04:30.415 align:middle line:90%


00:04:30.415 --> 00:04:31.915 align:middle line:10%
ILLOBRAND VON LUDWIGER
(THROUGH INTERPRETER):

00:04:31.915 --> 00:04:34.240 align:middle line:10%
When you know that science can't
come close to getting a handle

00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:38.010 align:middle line:10%
on the whole thing, then you
know why the press can't report

00:04:38.010 --> 00:04:39.280 align:middle line:10%
anything serious about it.

00:04:39.280 --> 00:04:42.730 align:middle line:90%


00:04:42.730 --> 00:04:44.150 align:middle line:84%
They only take an
interest in what

00:04:44.150 --> 00:04:47.790 align:middle line:84%
they know so that the
continuity of causality

00:04:47.790 --> 00:04:49.253 align:middle line:90%
won't be disruptive too much.

00:04:49.253 --> 00:05:03.550 align:middle line:90%


00:05:03.550 --> 00:05:07.300 align:middle line:90%
NARRATOR: 2012.

00:05:07.300 --> 00:05:12.720 align:middle line:84%
Almost no one is immune to
the magnetism of this date.

00:05:12.720 --> 00:05:17.210 align:middle line:84%
With all the crises and constant
outbreak of new conflicts,

00:05:17.210 --> 00:05:22.350 align:middle line:84%
sinister prophecies fan the
fires of apocalyptic angst.

00:05:22.350 --> 00:05:25.730 align:middle line:84%
While for others, the
promise of spiritual renewal

00:05:25.730 --> 00:05:27.820 align:middle line:84%
gives strength in
uncertain times.

00:05:27.820 --> 00:05:33.800 align:middle line:90%


00:05:33.800 --> 00:05:37.580 align:middle line:84%
What bothers me in both
scenarios, as a scientist,

00:05:37.580 --> 00:05:39.790 align:middle line:84%
is the mood of panic
and even hysteria

00:05:39.790 --> 00:05:42.350 align:middle line:90%
that often gets whipped up.

00:05:42.350 --> 00:05:46.610 align:middle line:84%
But I do find it remarkable that
in many ancient civilizations

00:05:46.610 --> 00:05:49.520 align:middle line:84%
this particular year
is believed to mark

00:05:49.520 --> 00:05:51.390 align:middle line:90%
a special turning point.

00:05:51.390 --> 00:05:55.040 align:middle line:84%
The Maya even refer
to it as the final,

00:05:55.040 --> 00:05:56.970 align:middle line:90%
all-encompassing transition.

00:05:56.970 --> 00:06:02.140 align:middle line:90%


00:06:02.140 --> 00:06:07.660 align:middle line:84%
And that is clearly already
well underway, isn't it?

00:06:07.660 --> 00:06:09.870 align:middle line:10%
We've long since
realized that all

00:06:09.870 --> 00:06:12.150 align:middle line:10%
the current global
challenges can only

00:06:12.150 --> 00:06:15.170 align:middle line:10%
be mastered if we break
through established

00:06:15.170 --> 00:06:17.850 align:middle line:10%
structures and habitual
ways of thinking

00:06:17.850 --> 00:06:19.775 align:middle line:10%
and develop a new awareness.

00:06:19.775 --> 00:06:29.194 align:middle line:90%


00:06:29.194 --> 00:06:31.690 align:middle line:84%
Furthermore, natural
scientists are now

00:06:31.690 --> 00:06:34.020 align:middle line:84%
observing that
cosmic influences are

00:06:34.020 --> 00:06:37.240 align:middle line:84%
having an increasing
effect on material,

00:06:37.240 --> 00:06:39.120 align:middle line:90%
environment, and ourselves.

00:06:39.120 --> 00:06:41.730 align:middle line:84%
Which in turn is a
measurable Influence

00:06:41.730 --> 00:06:43.165 align:middle line:90%
on our feelings and perception.

00:06:43.165 --> 00:06:50.780 align:middle line:90%


00:06:50.780 --> 00:06:52.780 align:middle line:10%
INTERPRETER: We're already in
a different state of awareness

00:06:52.780 --> 00:06:55.900 align:middle line:10%
now, wide awake, than we
just woke up only three,

00:06:55.900 --> 00:06:57.500 align:middle line:10%
four, five, six hours ago.

00:06:57.500 --> 00:06:59.090 align:middle line:90%
It's a different state of being.

00:06:59.090 --> 00:07:01.150 align:middle line:84%
Which is then expanded
to become a higher

00:07:01.150 --> 00:07:04.360 align:middle line:84%
level of consciousness, a level
that allows us to perceive

00:07:04.360 --> 00:07:05.840 align:middle line:90%
everything differently.

00:07:05.840 --> 00:07:07.950 align:middle line:84%
Including the things we've
already lived through.

00:07:07.950 --> 00:07:10.350 align:middle line:84%
The interaction between
you and me changes.

00:07:10.350 --> 00:07:12.830 align:middle line:84%
The physical separation
ceases to exist.

00:07:12.830 --> 00:07:14.850 align:middle line:84%
The idea that you're
over there and I am here

00:07:14.850 --> 00:07:16.700 align:middle line:90%
and you're something different.

00:07:16.700 --> 00:07:20.450 align:middle line:84%
It is the ability to perceive
the holistic nature of things.

00:07:20.450 --> 00:07:23.040 align:middle line:84%
I see that as an outcome
of this transformation.

00:07:23.040 --> 00:07:33.400 align:middle line:90%


00:07:33.400 --> 00:07:36.310 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: I myself have spent
many years focusing on how

00:07:36.310 --> 00:07:39.960 align:middle line:84%
to scientifically describe
how our bio-organism reacts

00:07:39.960 --> 00:07:43.400 align:middle line:84%
to terrestrial and
cosmic influences.

00:07:43.400 --> 00:07:45.235 align:middle line:84%
Electromagnetic
fields, for example.

00:07:45.235 --> 00:07:49.440 align:middle line:90%


00:07:49.440 --> 00:07:53.120 align:middle line:10%
The real sensation is that it
appears these research data

00:07:53.120 --> 00:07:56.940 align:middle line:10%
could take on an unprecedented
significance for humanity

00:07:56.940 --> 00:08:02.780 align:middle line:10%
in the period right
around 2012, of all times.

00:08:02.780 --> 00:08:05.360 align:middle line:84%
But that's just one
side of the coin.

00:08:05.360 --> 00:08:08.710 align:middle line:84%
Because if our perception
changes as dramatically as I

00:08:08.710 --> 00:08:13.670 align:middle line:84%
suspect is possible, our entire
world view will inevitably

00:08:13.670 --> 00:08:18.610 align:middle line:90%
be derailed as a result.

00:08:18.610 --> 00:08:20.160 align:middle line:84%
That's why we should
approach everything

00:08:20.160 --> 00:08:23.210 align:middle line:84%
that happens from here on
in with the consciousness

00:08:23.210 --> 00:08:24.530 align:middle line:90%
of a child.

00:08:24.530 --> 00:08:26.425 align:middle line:90%
Open and unbiased.

00:08:26.425 --> 00:08:29.740 align:middle line:90%


00:08:29.740 --> 00:08:32.799 align:middle line:10%
That will enable us to
open up a world in which

00:08:32.799 --> 00:08:36.500 align:middle line:10%
mathematicians become
philosophers and science

00:08:36.500 --> 00:08:37.659 align:middle line:10%
merges with religion.

00:08:37.659 --> 00:08:40.990 align:middle line:90%


00:08:40.990 --> 00:08:44.440 align:middle line:84%
And this way, we can begin now
to overcome the limitations

00:08:44.440 --> 00:08:47.200 align:middle line:84%
of our consciousness and
to breach the boundaries

00:08:47.200 --> 00:08:48.500 align:middle line:90%
of space and time.

00:08:48.500 --> 00:08:54.580 align:middle line:90%


00:08:54.580 --> 00:08:57.730 align:middle line:84%
To understand why our perception
and awareness could soon

00:08:57.730 --> 00:09:01.030 align:middle line:84%
undergo such a dramatic
change, we must first explore

00:09:01.030 --> 00:09:02.440 align:middle line:90%
a few fundamental questions.

00:09:02.440 --> 00:09:05.645 align:middle line:84%
Namely, what exactly
is consciousness?

00:09:05.645 --> 00:09:09.880 align:middle line:90%


00:09:09.880 --> 00:09:13.740 align:middle line:84%
Where is this inexplicable
part of our existence located,

00:09:13.740 --> 00:09:19.304 align:middle line:84%
and what role does our
brain play in this context?

00:09:19.304 --> 00:09:21.170 align:middle line:84%
RUPERT SHELDRAKE: And this
is one of the most unexplored

00:09:21.170 --> 00:09:23.170 align:middle line:90%
areas in all of science.

00:09:23.170 --> 00:09:24.780 align:middle line:84%
It's now one of
the most exciting

00:09:24.780 --> 00:09:29.390 align:middle line:84%
areas, consciousness studies,
is a frontier area of science.

00:09:29.390 --> 00:09:32.320 align:middle line:84%
Largely because consciousness
itself has been so ignored

00:09:32.320 --> 00:09:35.230 align:middle line:90%
by scientists for so long.

00:09:35.230 --> 00:09:37.160 align:middle line:10%
Now, at last, people
are looking at this

00:09:37.160 --> 00:09:39.620 align:middle line:10%
and realizing we
know almost nothing

00:09:39.620 --> 00:09:41.830 align:middle line:10%
about the nature
of our own minds

00:09:41.830 --> 00:09:43.220 align:middle line:10%
and how they relate
to our brains.

00:09:43.220 --> 00:09:52.830 align:middle line:90%


00:09:52.830 --> 00:09:55.710 align:middle line:84%
I'm interested in what I call
the mysteries of everyday life.

00:09:55.710 --> 00:09:59.220 align:middle line:84%
Things that happen to lots
of people but which science

00:09:59.220 --> 00:10:00.700 align:middle line:90%
can't explain.

00:10:00.700 --> 00:10:03.690 align:middle line:84%
One of them is telepathic
telephone calls.

00:10:03.690 --> 00:10:05.810 align:middle line:84%
You think of someone
and then they ring.

00:10:05.810 --> 00:10:08.620 align:middle line:84%
And then you say, that's funny,
I was just thinking about you.

00:10:08.620 --> 00:10:11.000 align:middle line:84%
More than 80 percent of people
have had that experience

00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:13.560 align:middle line:90%
in Europe and America.

00:10:13.560 --> 00:10:14.760 align:middle line:90%
So, it's very common.

00:10:14.760 --> 00:10:20.080 align:middle line:90%


00:10:20.080 --> 00:10:25.610 align:middle line:84%
Another area is the
feeling of being stared at.

00:10:25.610 --> 00:10:27.750 align:middle line:84%
You turn around,
somebody's looking at you.

00:10:27.750 --> 00:10:29.790 align:middle line:84%
Or you stare at someone,
they turn around.

00:10:29.790 --> 00:10:32.160 align:middle line:84%
Well, I've had these
experiences myself.

00:10:32.160 --> 00:10:35.400 align:middle line:84%
And again, most people have
the sense of being stared at.

00:10:35.400 --> 00:10:39.510 align:middle line:10%
About 90 percent of people have
had that experience, in a way

00:10:39.510 --> 00:10:41.780 align:middle line:10%
that seems to be telepathic.

00:10:41.780 --> 00:10:44.310 align:middle line:84%
So, I've done experiments
to find out whether it

00:10:44.310 --> 00:10:45.900 align:middle line:90%
really is telepathic.

00:10:45.900 --> 00:10:49.559 align:middle line:84%
And yes indeed, or at least
in some cases it seems to be.

00:10:49.559 --> 00:10:55.050 align:middle line:90%


00:10:55.050 --> 00:10:58.450 align:middle line:84%
The conventional view of the
materialist theory of the mind,

00:10:58.450 --> 00:11:02.150 align:middle line:84%
which is still the dominant
theory within academic science,

00:11:02.150 --> 00:11:03.910 align:middle line:90%
says that the mind is the brain.

00:11:03.910 --> 00:11:06.240 align:middle line:84%
Mental activity
is brain activity.

00:11:06.240 --> 00:11:11.490 align:middle line:84%
All your thoughts, intentions,
and so on are inside your head.

00:11:11.490 --> 00:11:14.690 align:middle line:84%
What I'm suggesting is they're
not all inside your head.

00:11:14.690 --> 00:11:17.020 align:middle line:84%
They extend beyond your
head through fields,

00:11:17.020 --> 00:11:18.697 align:middle line:90%
which I call morphic fields.

00:11:18.697 --> 00:11:24.770 align:middle line:90%


00:11:24.770 --> 00:11:26.610 align:middle line:84%
MICHAEL PERSINGER: The
interesting thing-- and we've

00:11:26.610 --> 00:11:30.110 align:middle line:84%
known it for years, but
somehow it eluded us-- that

00:11:30.110 --> 00:11:34.826 align:middle line:84%
for about 20 minutes during the
acquisition of new information,

00:11:34.826 --> 00:11:36.260 align:middle line:90%
that it's two stages.

00:11:36.260 --> 00:11:39.410 align:middle line:84%
It's electrical,
electromagnetic,

00:11:39.410 --> 00:11:42.110 align:middle line:90%
and its physical, chemical.

00:11:42.110 --> 00:11:45.620 align:middle line:10%
Its energy and matter.

00:11:45.620 --> 00:11:47.260 align:middle line:10%
And during that
15 to 20 minutes,

00:11:47.260 --> 00:11:50.220 align:middle line:10%
that pattern that
we call experience

00:11:50.220 --> 00:11:54.840 align:middle line:10%
is transformed into connections
on dendrites' spines

00:11:54.840 --> 00:11:55.650 align:middle line:10%
that connect.

00:11:55.650 --> 00:11:59.090 align:middle line:84%
And in a lifetime,
with all of the energy

00:11:59.090 --> 00:12:00.810 align:middle line:84%
associated for your
thinking, that's

00:12:00.810 --> 00:12:02.710 align:middle line:90%
just a few joules of energy.

00:12:02.710 --> 00:12:04.690 align:middle line:90%
That's the thinking.

00:12:04.690 --> 00:12:07.440 align:middle line:84%
And the Earth's magnetic
field has the capacity

00:12:07.440 --> 00:12:10.880 align:middle line:90%
to store 10 to the 18th joules.

00:12:10.880 --> 00:12:14.510 align:middle line:84%
Which means that the thought of
every person who has ever lived

00:12:14.510 --> 00:12:16.950 align:middle line:90%
could be there, represented.

00:12:16.950 --> 00:12:20.050 align:middle line:84%
So, all this idea says
is that information-- not

00:12:20.050 --> 00:12:21.850 align:middle line:90%
you, not your sense of self.

00:12:21.850 --> 00:12:23.520 align:middle line:90%
That's a brain phenomenon.

00:12:23.520 --> 00:12:26.540 align:middle line:84%
But the information is
stored extracerebrally.

00:12:26.540 --> 00:12:28.138 align:middle line:90%


00:12:28.138 --> 00:12:29.404 align:middle line:84%
ERNST SENKOWSKI
(THROUGH INTERPRETER):

00:12:29.404 --> 00:12:32.870 align:middle line:84%
In quantum theory, we talk about
statistics and probabilities

00:12:32.870 --> 00:12:35.130 align:middle line:90%
and basically about noise.

00:12:35.130 --> 00:12:38.940 align:middle line:84%
We have a constant background
noise that is simply there.

00:12:38.940 --> 00:12:41.240 align:middle line:10%
What we do with our
brain is to pull

00:12:41.240 --> 00:12:43.640 align:middle line:10%
information out of this noise.

00:12:43.640 --> 00:12:45.680 align:middle line:10%
In that sense,
anything at all can

00:12:45.680 --> 00:12:48.420 align:middle line:10%
be found in the noise field.

00:12:48.420 --> 00:12:52.500 align:middle line:84%
So, from out of other space-time
or non-space-time areas,

00:12:52.500 --> 00:12:56.280 align:middle line:84%
these information fields
control, [INAUDIBLE],

00:12:56.280 --> 00:13:00.070 align:middle line:84%
the activity here on Earth,
with the help of processes

00:13:00.070 --> 00:13:01.790 align:middle line:90%
that occur in our brains.

00:13:01.790 --> 00:13:05.102 align:middle line:90%


00:13:05.102 --> 00:13:05.825 align:middle line:90%
NARRATOR: Our brain.

00:13:05.825 --> 00:13:09.500 align:middle line:90%


00:13:09.500 --> 00:13:14.350 align:middle line:84%
A package of wonders that we
haven't even unpacked yet.

00:13:14.350 --> 00:13:17.380 align:middle line:84%
It's unfathomable, but the
number of possible connections

00:13:17.380 --> 00:13:20.950 align:middle line:84%
in the brain is greater than
the number of all the atoms

00:13:20.950 --> 00:13:24.620 align:middle line:90%
in the entire universe.

00:13:24.620 --> 00:13:27.430 align:middle line:84%
We know the various
messenger substances, known

00:13:27.430 --> 00:13:30.880 align:middle line:84%
as neurotransmitters, are
responsible for the exchange

00:13:30.880 --> 00:13:33.302 align:middle line:84%
of information
between nerve cells.

00:13:33.302 --> 00:13:36.200 align:middle line:90%


00:13:36.200 --> 00:13:39.400 align:middle line:84%
Minute electrical impulses
prompt the nerve cell

00:13:39.400 --> 00:13:41.970 align:middle line:84%
to discharge these
neurotransmitters, which

00:13:41.970 --> 00:13:44.310 align:middle line:84%
are made up of different
specific molecules

00:13:44.310 --> 00:13:47.440 align:middle line:84%
according to their
particular function.

00:13:47.440 --> 00:13:50.950 align:middle line:84%
It is these molecules that keep
our feelings, and our lives,

00:13:50.950 --> 00:13:53.750 align:middle line:90%
in rhythm.

00:13:53.750 --> 00:13:57.080 align:middle line:84%
They control the sleeping and
waking phases of the body,

00:13:57.080 --> 00:13:59.085 align:middle line:84%
and trigger euphoria
and depression.

00:13:59.085 --> 00:14:04.900 align:middle line:90%


00:14:04.900 --> 00:14:07.720 align:middle line:90%
So far, so good.

00:14:07.720 --> 00:14:10.700 align:middle line:84%
But this purely
biochemical analysis

00:14:10.700 --> 00:14:13.460 align:middle line:84%
doesn't explain why our
feeling of self identity

00:14:13.460 --> 00:14:16.480 align:middle line:84%
develops with the
accompanying experiences

00:14:16.480 --> 00:14:19.070 align:middle line:90%
and intuitive events.

00:14:19.070 --> 00:14:21.920 align:middle line:84%
This is where biology
reaches its limits.

00:14:21.920 --> 00:14:24.750 align:middle line:84%
And consciousness research
becomes the subject

00:14:24.750 --> 00:14:27.290 align:middle line:84%
of a discipline that has
historically focused more

00:14:27.290 --> 00:14:30.120 align:middle line:84%
than any other unmeasurable
characteristics

00:14:30.120 --> 00:14:32.625 align:middle line:90%
and immutable laws-- physics.

00:14:32.625 --> 00:14:37.020 align:middle line:90%


