So the solar wind
plucks the field lines,

00:24:35.350 --> 00:24:36.790 align:middle line:90%
very much like a guitar string.

00:24:36.790 --> 00:24:40.320 align:middle line:90%


00:24:40.320 --> 00:24:42.540 align:middle line:84%
The Schumann resonances
are determined

00:24:42.540 --> 00:24:45.940 align:middle line:84%
by the resonate cavity between
the surface of the earth

00:24:45.940 --> 00:24:48.660 align:middle line:84%
and basically the bottom
of the ionosphere.

00:24:48.660 --> 00:24:52.660 align:middle line:84%
So when the magnetic waves get
established in this cavity,

00:24:52.660 --> 00:24:55.120 align:middle line:84%
those that are resonant
with the resonant frequency

00:24:55.120 --> 00:24:59.940 align:middle line:84%
of the cavity become globally
propagating standing waves.

00:24:59.940 --> 00:25:03.040 align:middle line:84%
And there are eight primary
Schumann resonances.

00:25:03.040 --> 00:25:05.980 align:middle line:84%
The first one is 7.8
Hertz, and that's

00:25:05.980 --> 00:25:08.100 align:middle line:84%
very close to what's
called the alpha rhythm

00:25:08.100 --> 00:25:10.280 align:middle line:90%
in our brain waves.

00:25:10.280 --> 00:25:13.490 align:middle line:84%
It turns out all eight of these
primary Schumann resonances

00:25:13.490 --> 00:25:15.375 align:middle line:84%
have overlaps with
human brain waves.

00:25:15.375 --> 00:25:20.030 align:middle line:90%


00:25:20.030 --> 00:25:23.120 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: Of course we cannot
perceive the geomagnetic field

00:25:23.120 --> 00:25:24.850 align:middle line:90%
directly with our five senses.

00:25:24.850 --> 00:25:29.150 align:middle line:84%
Yet, we do have the
antennas for it.

00:25:29.150 --> 00:25:32.650 align:middle line:90%


00:25:32.650 --> 00:25:34.700 align:middle line:84%
We have at our
disposal more than 5

00:25:34.700 --> 00:25:39.630 align:middle line:84%
million magnetite crystals
per gram of brain mass.

00:25:39.630 --> 00:25:43.440 align:middle line:84%
They react extremely sensitively
to all the magnetic fields

00:25:43.440 --> 00:25:46.950 align:middle line:84%
in our environment and very
significantly to sudden change.

00:25:46.950 --> 00:25:50.360 align:middle line:90%


00:25:50.360 --> 00:25:54.290 align:middle line:10%
When there are magnetic
storms, these magnetic storms

00:25:54.290 --> 00:25:58.400 align:middle line:10%
can play havoc with satellites.

00:25:58.400 --> 00:26:01.330 align:middle line:84%
Communication
satellites, for instance.

00:26:01.330 --> 00:26:05.570 align:middle line:84%
This has been the reason why
there have been some blackouts.

00:26:05.570 --> 00:26:09.650 align:middle line:90%


00:26:09.650 --> 00:26:13.540 align:middle line:84%
Now if you look at what is the
physiology of an individual,

00:26:13.540 --> 00:26:19.780 align:middle line:84%
well, the heart is a very
big electrical circuit.

00:26:19.780 --> 00:26:23.200 align:middle line:90%
It's a big pump.

00:26:23.200 --> 00:26:26.530 align:middle line:84%
The brain also has
electrical activity.

00:26:26.530 --> 00:26:29.890 align:middle line:84%
So there is no reason to
believe that they will act any

00:26:29.890 --> 00:26:33.880 align:middle line:84%
differently from the
grid of the satellites

00:26:33.880 --> 00:26:35.690 align:middle line:84%
when they're hit by
a magnetic storm.

00:26:35.690 --> 00:26:41.660 align:middle line:90%


00:26:41.660 --> 00:26:44.070 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: Statistical
evaluations are in fact

00:26:44.070 --> 00:26:47.810 align:middle line:84%
making it clear that disruptions
in the geomagnetic field

00:26:47.810 --> 00:26:51.350 align:middle line:84%
are reflected in just
about all areas of life.

00:26:51.350 --> 00:26:54.640 align:middle line:90%


00:26:54.640 --> 00:27:00.748 align:middle line:84%
Birth rate, industrial
accidents, death statistics,

00:27:00.748 --> 00:27:02.460 align:middle line:90%
traffic accidents.

00:27:02.460 --> 00:27:05.260 align:middle line:10%
The numbers are always
way above average on days

00:27:05.260 --> 00:27:07.730 align:middle line:10%
when extreme geomagnetic
activity is recorded.

00:27:07.730 --> 00:27:12.810 align:middle line:90%


00:27:12.810 --> 00:27:15.280 align:middle line:84%
A study commissioned by
the US Federal Reserve

00:27:15.280 --> 00:27:19.310 align:middle line:84%
concluded that even trade on the
international stock exchanges

00:27:19.310 --> 00:27:22.030 align:middle line:84%
is influenced directly
by the activity

00:27:22.030 --> 00:27:23.560 align:middle line:90%
of the geomagnetic field.

00:27:23.560 --> 00:27:51.070 align:middle line:90%


00:27:51.070 --> 00:27:54.580 align:middle line:84%
It now appears certain
the geomagnetic field

00:27:54.580 --> 00:27:57.390 align:middle line:84%
seems to have a decisive
effect on our psyche

00:27:57.390 --> 00:27:58.143 align:middle line:90%
and our biorhythms.

00:27:58.143 --> 00:28:03.280 align:middle line:90%


00:28:03.280 --> 00:28:09.210 align:middle line:84%
What does that mean in relation
to the year 2012 and beyond?

00:28:09.210 --> 00:28:12.530 align:middle line:84%
For the biophysical and
chemical processes in our brain

00:28:12.530 --> 00:28:15.140 align:middle line:84%
to change in the way
that we have observed

00:28:15.140 --> 00:28:17.910 align:middle line:84%
in our experiments
with artificial fields,

00:28:17.910 --> 00:28:21.199 align:middle line:84%
very dramatic geomagnetic
turbulence would

00:28:21.199 --> 00:28:22.974 align:middle line:90%
have to occur around this time.

00:28:22.974 --> 00:28:28.790 align:middle line:90%


00:28:28.790 --> 00:28:31.820 align:middle line:84%
Is a calculable,
perhaps cyclical event

00:28:31.820 --> 00:28:33.530 align:middle line:84%
actually due to
take place that will

00:28:33.530 --> 00:28:34.770 align:middle line:90%
have an effect on our planet?

00:28:34.770 --> 00:28:38.250 align:middle line:90%


00:28:38.250 --> 00:28:40.970 align:middle line:84%
We know now that in the
history of the Earth

00:28:40.970 --> 00:28:43.860 align:middle line:84%
there have been regular
incidences of extreme changes

00:28:43.860 --> 00:28:45.470 align:middle line:90%
to the magnetic field.

00:28:45.470 --> 00:28:48.700 align:middle line:84%
These things appear to be
due to regular cosmic cycles,

00:28:48.700 --> 00:28:50.220 align:middle line:90%
comparable to the four seasons.

00:28:50.220 --> 00:28:59.800 align:middle line:90%


00:28:59.800 --> 00:29:03.620 align:middle line:84%
At this point in the discussion,
the Mayan calendar must

00:29:03.620 --> 00:29:06.130 align:middle line:90%
inevitably enter the equation.

00:29:06.130 --> 00:29:09.190 align:middle line:84%
According to their
calculations, our year 2012

00:29:09.190 --> 00:29:13.340 align:middle line:84%
is so special precisely because
this is when various cycles

00:29:13.340 --> 00:29:16.630 align:middle line:90%
end and also begin.

00:29:16.630 --> 00:29:18.700 align:middle line:90%
It's comparable to a clock face.

00:29:18.700 --> 00:29:21.290 align:middle line:84%
Once every 12 hours
all three hands

00:29:21.290 --> 00:29:24.840 align:middle line:84%
point to 12 for the short
duration of one second.

00:29:24.840 --> 00:29:32.670 align:middle line:90%


00:29:32.670 --> 00:29:36.522 align:middle line:84%
So let's take a closer look at
the cosmic cycles known today.

00:29:36.522 --> 00:29:40.250 align:middle line:90%


00:29:40.250 --> 00:29:42.125 align:middle line:84%
We are made aware of
them most consciously

00:29:42.125 --> 00:29:44.550 align:middle line:84%
by the alternation
of day and night,

00:29:44.550 --> 00:29:48.550 align:middle line:84%
caused by the rotation of
the Earth on its own axis.

00:29:48.550 --> 00:29:52.032 align:middle line:84%
Indisputably, the most
self evident of all cycles.

00:29:52.032 --> 00:29:57.700 align:middle line:90%


00:29:57.700 --> 00:30:00.500 align:middle line:84%
Just as obvious is
the unit of the month.

00:30:00.500 --> 00:30:04.770 align:middle line:84%
Our moon orbits the earth
once in exactly 28 days.

00:30:04.770 --> 00:30:07.790 align:middle line:84%
We can clearly observe this
in the various moon phases.

00:30:07.790 --> 00:30:15.065 align:middle line:90%


00:30:15.065 --> 00:30:20.780 align:middle line:84%
Our Earth takes 365 days for
its journey around the sun.

00:30:20.780 --> 00:30:22.600 align:middle line:90%
In other words, one year.

00:30:22.600 --> 00:30:25.710 align:middle line:84%
The sequence of four seasons
arises over the course

00:30:25.710 --> 00:30:28.300 align:middle line:84%
of the one cycle due
to the slight tilt

00:30:28.300 --> 00:30:30.690 align:middle line:90%
of our Earth on its axis.

00:30:30.690 --> 00:30:32.590 align:middle line:84%
The hemisphere tilted
towards the sun

00:30:32.590 --> 00:30:36.010 align:middle line:84%
is somewhat warmer because the
sun's rays hit it a sharper

00:30:36.010 --> 00:30:38.850 align:middle line:84%
angle and also because
the days are significantly

00:30:38.850 --> 00:30:40.345 align:middle line:90%
longer there than the nights.

00:30:40.345 --> 00:30:44.074 align:middle line:90%
In this hemisphere, it's summer.

00:30:44.074 --> 00:30:46.980 align:middle line:84%
But our Earth's
axis doesn't always

00:30:46.980 --> 00:30:49.130 align:middle line:90%
tilt in the same direction.

00:30:49.130 --> 00:30:51.880 align:middle line:84%
A cycle that can only be
observed over millennia

00:30:51.880 --> 00:30:54.970 align:middle line:84%
is the procession
of the equinoxes,

00:30:54.970 --> 00:30:57.140 align:middle line:90%
also known as a platonic year.

00:30:57.140 --> 00:30:59.830 align:middle line:84%
Our Earth wobbles like
a slow-spinning top,

00:30:59.830 --> 00:31:04.190 align:middle line:84%
and it takes around 26,000 years
until the Earth's axis tilts

00:31:04.190 --> 00:31:05.453 align:middle line:90%
in the same direction again.

00:31:05.453 --> 00:31:09.620 align:middle line:90%


00:31:09.620 --> 00:31:12.490 align:middle line:84%
All of these processes,
which we can confirm

00:31:12.490 --> 00:31:15.140 align:middle line:84%
with ultra-modern
instruments at best,

00:31:15.140 --> 00:31:17.580 align:middle line:84%
were already well
known to the Maya

00:31:17.580 --> 00:31:21.200 align:middle line:84%
and formed the basis of
their cyclical calendar.

00:31:21.200 --> 00:31:22.850 align:middle line:84%
Thanks to this
knowledge, they were

00:31:22.850 --> 00:31:24.950 align:middle line:84%
able to give each
day for centuries

00:31:24.950 --> 00:31:28.630 align:middle line:90%
ahead its own individual name.

00:31:28.630 --> 00:31:31.920 align:middle line:84%
That's very important when
you assume, as did the Maya,

00:31:31.920 --> 00:31:35.500 align:middle line:84%
that each day comes with its
own particular quality due to

00:31:35.500 --> 00:31:37.170 align:middle line:90%
the exact cosmic constellation.

00:31:37.170 --> 00:31:40.292 align:middle line:90%


00:31:40.292 --> 00:31:42.905 align:middle line:84%
But returning to the
subject of cosmic cycles.

00:31:42.905 --> 00:31:45.570 align:middle line:90%


00:31:45.570 --> 00:31:47.770 align:middle line:84%
Our entire planetary
system orbits

00:31:47.770 --> 00:31:51.940 align:middle line:84%
around the center of our galaxy
over an unimaginably long

00:31:51.940 --> 00:31:52.870 align:middle line:90%
period of time.

00:31:52.870 --> 00:31:55.750 align:middle line:90%


00:31:55.750 --> 00:31:58.170 align:middle line:84%
At the same time,
it also oscillates

00:31:58.170 --> 00:32:01.280 align:middle line:90%
around the galactic equator.

00:32:01.280 --> 00:32:03.120 align:middle line:84%
In this case too,
the length of time

00:32:03.120 --> 00:32:05.010 align:middle line:84%
it takes for our
planetary system

00:32:05.010 --> 00:32:07.770 align:middle line:84%
to complete one cycle
of rising and sinking

00:32:07.770 --> 00:32:12.646 align:middle line:84%
is virtually unfathomable
in human terms.

00:32:12.646 --> 00:32:14.370 align:middle line:84%
According to the
Mayan calendar--

00:32:14.370 --> 00:32:17.030 align:middle line:84%
the perfect depiction
of cosmic cycles--

00:32:17.030 --> 00:32:20.850 align:middle line:84%
many such significant cycles are
expected to begin to dovetail

00:32:20.850 --> 00:32:23.460 align:middle line:90%
dramatically in the year 2012.

00:32:23.460 --> 00:32:26.390 align:middle line:84%
Resulting in a
constellation so unusual

00:32:26.390 --> 00:32:28.590 align:middle line:84%
that it will lead
to global changes

00:32:28.590 --> 00:32:33.190 align:middle line:84%
and the much-discussed
higher vibrational level.

00:32:33.190 --> 00:32:35.200 align:middle line:84%
However, there's
almost nothing we

00:32:35.200 --> 00:32:38.165 align:middle line:84%
can deduce with certainty from
the cycles known to us today.

00:32:38.165 --> 00:32:48.762 align:middle line:90%


00:32:48.762 --> 00:32:50.240 align:middle line:90%
[FLASH]

00:32:50.240 --> 00:32:52.330 align:middle line:84%
Even though some
current measurements

00:32:52.330 --> 00:32:55.980 align:middle line:84%
do seem to support such
prophecies-- increases

00:32:55.980 --> 00:32:59.500 align:middle line:84%
in cosmic radiation over
many years, for example--

00:32:59.500 --> 00:33:01.550 align:middle line:84%
the time frame and
distance in question

00:33:01.550 --> 00:33:05.210 align:middle line:84%
are still far too vast to
enable us to pin these events

00:33:05.210 --> 00:33:08.200 align:middle line:84%
down to a certain year,
let alone an exact day.

00:33:08.200 --> 00:33:10.770 align:middle line:90%


00:33:10.770 --> 00:33:14.340 align:middle line:84%
And it's completely unnecessary
for us to rely on speculation

00:33:14.340 --> 00:33:18.010 align:middle line:84%
because what is presumably
the most significant source

00:33:18.010 --> 00:33:22.410 align:middle line:84%
of geomagnetic disturbances,
in the cosmic sense as well,

00:33:22.410 --> 00:33:25.490 align:middle line:90%
is glaringly obvious.

00:33:25.490 --> 00:33:28.924 align:middle line:84%
It is a tiny cog in the
wheel of cosmic cycles,

00:33:28.924 --> 00:33:32.792 align:middle line:84%
yet powerful enough to cause
devastating economic and

00:33:32.792 --> 00:33:34.966 align:middle line:90%
material damage on our planet.

00:33:34.966 --> 00:33:38.950 align:middle line:90%


00:33:38.950 --> 00:33:43.432 align:middle line:90%
And the little cog is our sun.

00:33:43.432 --> 00:33:47.416 align:middle line:90%


