NARRATOR: In December
1995, NASA and ESA launched

00:34:39.280 --> 00:34:42.480 align:middle line:90%
the SOHO satellite into space.

00:34:42.480 --> 00:34:46.914 align:middle line:84%
SOHO, which stands for solar
and heliospheric observatory,

00:34:46.914 --> 00:34:50.361 align:middle line:84%
has since then sent us a steady
stream of measurement data

00:34:50.361 --> 00:34:51.060 align:middle line:90%
from the sun.

00:34:51.060 --> 00:34:58.275 align:middle line:90%


00:34:58.275 --> 00:35:02.620 align:middle line:84%
In 2006, a new era of
solar observation quality

00:35:02.620 --> 00:35:06.870 align:middle line:84%
was ushered in with the dual
satellites called STEREO.

00:35:06.870 --> 00:35:10.060 align:middle line:84%
These two satellites observe
the sun simultaneously

00:35:10.060 --> 00:35:11.510 align:middle line:90%
from different angles.

00:35:11.510 --> 00:35:14.690 align:middle line:84%
Like a giant pair of human
eyes, the STEREO mission

00:35:14.690 --> 00:35:17.310 align:middle line:84%
gives us an unprecedented
spatial view

00:35:17.310 --> 00:35:19.080 align:middle line:90%
of our central celestial body.

00:35:19.080 --> 00:35:28.890 align:middle line:90%


00:35:28.890 --> 00:35:32.600 align:middle line:84%
The research focuses on the
observation of explosions

00:35:32.600 --> 00:35:34.510 align:middle line:90%
on the sun's surface.

00:35:34.510 --> 00:35:38.670 align:middle line:84%
These solar flares, or
eruptions, catapult high energy

00:35:38.670 --> 00:35:42.110 align:middle line:84%
charge carriers into space
at speeds of several million

00:35:42.110 --> 00:35:43.200 align:middle line:90%
kilometers per hour.

00:35:43.200 --> 00:35:46.380 align:middle line:90%


00:35:46.380 --> 00:35:49.910 align:middle line:10%
A coronal mass ejection
is the violent expulsion

00:35:49.910 --> 00:35:52.770 align:middle line:10%
of part of the solar
atmosphere that contains

00:35:52.770 --> 00:35:55.200 align:middle line:10%
both magnetic field and plasma.

00:35:55.200 --> 00:36:05.020 align:middle line:90%


00:36:05.020 --> 00:36:07.640 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: Our Earth's
magnetic field protects us

00:36:07.640 --> 00:36:10.080 align:middle line:84%
from these particles,
diverting them

00:36:10.080 --> 00:36:13.780 align:middle line:90%
into a detour around the globe.

00:36:13.780 --> 00:36:15.720 align:middle line:84%
This causes an
effect which we can

00:36:15.720 --> 00:36:18.340 align:middle line:84%
observe at both of
the Earth's poles,

00:36:18.340 --> 00:36:19.995 align:middle line:90%
known as the Northern Lights.

00:36:19.995 --> 00:36:25.080 align:middle line:90%


00:36:25.080 --> 00:36:29.590 align:middle line:84%
But behind what we experience
as a spectacular show of nature

00:36:29.590 --> 00:36:31.500 align:middle line:90%
lurks an unpleasant shadow.

00:36:31.500 --> 00:36:34.780 align:middle line:90%


00:36:34.780 --> 00:36:36.180 align:middle line:84%
ANGELOS VOURLIDAS:
They can really disrupt

00:36:36.180 --> 00:36:37.790 align:middle line:90%
satellite communications.

00:36:37.790 --> 00:36:42.210 align:middle line:84%
They can affect GPS
signals, our cellphones.

00:36:42.210 --> 00:36:44.790 align:middle line:84%
They can even induce
a lot of currents

00:36:44.790 --> 00:36:46.350 align:middle line:84%
in the northern
latitudes and even

00:36:46.350 --> 00:36:48.815 align:middle line:90%
cause electricity disruptions.

00:36:48.815 --> 00:36:53.210 align:middle line:90%


00:36:53.210 --> 00:36:54.540 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: The
probability of what's

00:36:54.540 --> 00:36:57.970 align:middle line:84%
called a solar
superstorm is especially

00:36:57.970 --> 00:36:59.396 align:middle line:90%
high in the next few years.

00:36:59.396 --> 00:37:02.540 align:middle line:90%


00:37:02.540 --> 00:37:05.390 align:middle line:84%
NASA's solar researchers
have classified

00:37:05.390 --> 00:37:08.280 align:middle line:84%
the maximum solar activity
expected during this time

00:37:08.280 --> 00:37:11.590 align:middle line:84%
period as so
dangerous that in 2009

00:37:11.590 --> 00:37:13.510 align:middle line:84%
they began to issue
official warnings

00:37:13.510 --> 00:37:17.070 align:middle line:90%
about its possible effects.

00:37:17.070 --> 00:37:18.979 align:middle line:90%
Just stirring up panic?

00:37:18.979 --> 00:37:27.610 align:middle line:90%


00:37:27.610 --> 00:37:30.890 align:middle line:84%
Statistics show a clear
parallel at all times

00:37:30.890 --> 00:37:36.260 align:middle line:84%
between population rates on
earth and sunspot activity.

00:37:36.260 --> 00:37:38.420 align:middle line:84%
Further indication of
the strong corollary

00:37:38.420 --> 00:37:40.430 align:middle line:84%
between the reactions
of our climate

00:37:40.430 --> 00:37:45.000 align:middle line:84%
and all biological life
on Earth to solar cycle.

00:37:45.000 --> 00:37:49.350 align:middle line:10%
There is a bulk of
supporting evidence making

00:37:49.350 --> 00:37:53.130 align:middle line:10%
the whole story consistent.

00:37:53.130 --> 00:37:55.880 align:middle line:84%
And that is very important
because every cycle

00:37:55.880 --> 00:38:04.650 align:middle line:84%
that we map, every effect that
you find that may be associated

00:38:04.650 --> 00:38:10.500 align:middle line:84%
with solar activity or
other cycles that exist

