I think that there are
so many possibilities,

00:51:20.160 --> 00:51:22.390 align:middle line:10%
I think that sometimes
the limits are

00:51:22.390 --> 00:51:24.900 align:middle line:10%
the limits of our imagination.

00:51:24.900 --> 00:51:29.190 align:middle line:84%
Lord Kelvin suggested
that in 1899 no one

00:51:29.190 --> 00:51:31.660 align:middle line:84%
go into physics because
it was discovering

00:51:31.660 --> 00:51:35.250 align:middle line:90%
one more decimal place.

00:51:35.250 --> 00:51:37.960 align:middle line:84%
In the first case, I
don't think Billy Gates

00:51:37.960 --> 00:51:42.020 align:middle line:84%
and a lot of people, like
Tesla and Edison ands others,

00:51:42.020 --> 00:51:46.120 align:middle line:84%
noticed that everything
had been invented.

00:51:46.120 --> 00:51:47.880 align:middle line:90%
Man, were they wrong.

00:51:47.880 --> 00:51:50.665 align:middle line:90%
747's and everything.

00:51:50.665 --> 00:51:52.165 align:middle line:84%
ILLOBRAND VON LUDWIGER
(THROUGH INTERPRETER):

00:51:52.165 --> 00:51:54.460 align:middle line:84%
The whole focus
of scientific work

00:51:54.460 --> 00:51:56.670 align:middle line:90%
is to communicate certainties.

00:51:56.670 --> 00:51:58.820 align:middle line:90%
Not truths, certainties.

00:51:58.820 --> 00:52:00.315 align:middle line:84%
People feel safe
within certainties.

00:52:00.315 --> 00:52:05.240 align:middle line:90%


00:52:05.240 --> 00:52:07.510 align:middle line:10%
FRANCINE BLAKE: I was
always struck by the Romans

00:52:07.510 --> 00:52:12.060 align:middle line:10%
at the end of the Empire when
they said, if the Vandals come

00:52:12.060 --> 00:52:14.760 align:middle line:10%
and destroy-- and
attack us, it will

00:52:14.760 --> 00:52:18.299 align:middle line:10%
be the end of civilization.

00:52:18.299 --> 00:52:19.465 align:middle line:10%
Well, I mean, you
look the back now

00:52:19.465 --> 00:52:22.470 align:middle line:10%
and you say, what kind
of horrible civilization

00:52:22.470 --> 00:52:23.580 align:middle line:10%
did they have really?

00:52:23.580 --> 00:52:27.110 align:middle line:84%
Thank God the Vandals
came and wiped them out.

00:52:27.110 --> 00:52:30.821 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, who would want
to be stuck in that mindset?

00:52:30.821 --> 00:52:33.010 align:middle line:84%
Yeah?
It was horrible.

00:52:33.010 --> 00:52:33.860 align:middle line:90%
It's the same now.

00:52:33.860 --> 00:52:35.940 align:middle line:84%
We're so, oh, my God,
if something happens

00:52:35.940 --> 00:52:38.890 align:middle line:84%
we'll lose our civ-- what
civilization have we got

00:52:38.890 --> 00:52:40.974 align:middle line:90%
now to crow about, you know?

00:52:40.974 --> 00:52:46.670 align:middle line:90%


00:52:46.670 --> 00:52:50.080 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: Without a doubt, our
economic and social systems

00:52:50.080 --> 00:52:52.290 align:middle line:90%
are coming apart at the seams.

00:52:52.290 --> 00:52:54.880 align:middle line:84%
We debate daily about
environmental protection

00:52:54.880 --> 00:52:57.470 align:middle line:84%
and the necessity of doing
away with hunger and poverty

00:52:57.470 --> 00:52:58.780 align:middle line:90%
in the world.

00:52:58.780 --> 00:53:00.600 align:middle line:84%
But we're going
in circles trying

00:53:00.600 --> 00:53:02.270 align:middle line:84%
to protect the
environment using up

00:53:02.270 --> 00:53:04.600 align:middle line:90%
more resources in the process.

00:53:04.600 --> 00:53:07.050 align:middle line:84%
Helping the poor and hindering
them at the same time

00:53:07.050 --> 00:53:10.610 align:middle line:84%
from escaping poverty
on their own initiative.

00:53:10.610 --> 00:53:13.170 align:middle line:84%
All the while, our
instinct tells us

00:53:13.170 --> 00:53:17.300 align:middle line:84%
that nothing can change as
long as our worldview stays

00:53:17.300 --> 00:53:18.206 align:middle line:90%
the same.

00:53:18.206 --> 00:53:21.830 align:middle line:90%


00:53:21.830 --> 00:53:23.960 align:middle line:84%
So we need evermore
new solutions

00:53:23.960 --> 00:53:26.930 align:middle line:84%
for problems that were
the result of solutions

00:53:26.930 --> 00:53:29.740 align:middle line:84%
to other problems
in the first place.

00:53:29.740 --> 00:53:31.710 align:middle line:84%
We've never really
learned to let

00:53:31.710 --> 00:53:33.864 align:middle line:90%
go and recognize the causes.

00:53:33.864 --> 00:53:39.078 align:middle line:90%


00:53:39.078 --> 00:53:42.661 align:middle line:84%
All our belief systems
were very, very restrictive.

00:53:42.661 --> 00:53:43.360 align:middle line:90%
All of them.

00:53:43.360 --> 00:53:46.690 align:middle line:84%
The church had the power of
life and death and so on.

00:53:46.690 --> 00:53:48.710 align:middle line:84%
Science was supposed
to be our saving grace

00:53:48.710 --> 00:53:52.770 align:middle line:84%
and is becoming very dogmatic
as well now in a similar way.

00:53:52.770 --> 00:53:56.180 align:middle line:84%
And the application of science
is seriously dangerous.

00:53:56.180 --> 00:53:59.053 align:middle line:84%
So, we've got all this
to come out of, you know?

00:53:59.053 --> 00:54:02.730 align:middle line:84%
And people think
this is all there is,

00:54:02.730 --> 00:54:04.760 align:middle line:84%
and they're used to
being constricted.

00:54:04.760 --> 00:54:08.740 align:middle line:84%
Physicists talk about a
final theory of everything.

00:54:08.740 --> 00:54:10.700 align:middle line:84%
Whenever you think
you know everything,

00:54:10.700 --> 00:54:13.420 align:middle line:90%
you're in for a rude awakening.

00:54:13.420 --> 00:54:17.230 align:middle line:84%
And I think that the glory of
it all is that we don't know

00:54:17.230 --> 00:54:19.090 align:middle line:90%
everything, and it's wonderful.

00:54:19.090 --> 00:54:22.720 align:middle line:84%
Because in our discoveries
we have the possibility

00:54:22.720 --> 00:54:26.930 align:middle line:84%
of not only creating a
more Utopian society,

00:54:26.930 --> 00:54:29.140 align:middle line:84%
but getting in touch
with how we can

00:54:29.140 --> 00:54:31.190 align:middle line:84%
have peace, love,
and joy instead

00:54:31.190 --> 00:54:33.760 align:middle line:90%
of war, crime, and violence.

00:54:33.760 --> 00:54:36.980 align:middle line:84%
And it's going to be very
difficult for a lot of people

00:54:36.980 --> 00:54:38.820 align:middle line:84%
to just suddenly let
go of that and be

00:54:38.820 --> 00:54:43.820 align:middle line:84%
free and be able to function
in a different reality.

00:54:43.820 --> 00:54:45.960 align:middle line:90%
They won't want to, probably.

00:54:45.960 --> 00:54:48.310 align:middle line:84%
Most of them, a lot
of them won't want to.

00:54:48.310 --> 00:54:52.030 align:middle line:84%
The major impedance
of this is science.

00:54:52.030 --> 00:54:56.100 align:middle line:84%
Science has become very
narrow, very restricted.

00:54:56.100 --> 00:55:00.790 align:middle line:84%
And the fact that there could
be new phenomena, phenomena

00:55:00.790 --> 00:55:03.490 align:middle line:84%
that we haven't imagined,
is a very difficult thing

00:55:03.490 --> 00:55:07.690 align:middle line:84%
for many contemporary
scientists to understand

00:55:07.690 --> 00:55:09.940 align:middle line:90%
or appreciate or even accept.

00:55:09.940 --> 00:55:11.940 align:middle line:84%
It's just a matter of
time because the younger

00:55:11.940 --> 00:55:14.300 align:middle line:84%
generations are more
open than the older ones.

00:55:14.300 --> 00:55:17.580 align:middle line:84%
As Max Planck said, for such
paradigm shifts to occur,

00:55:17.580 --> 00:55:20.360 align:middle line:84%
you have to wait until old
ones die out for the young ones

00:55:20.360 --> 00:55:21.195 align:middle line:90%
to do things differently.

00:55:21.195 --> 00:55:24.860 align:middle line:90%


00:55:24.860 --> 00:55:27.730 align:middle line:84%
FRANZ HALBERG: Dealing
with the cosmos

00:55:27.730 --> 00:55:33.670 align:middle line:84%
and ourselves means
dealing with our problems.

00:55:33.670 --> 00:55:39.330 align:middle line:10%
So, when we discuss cancer or
high blood pressure or strokes,

00:55:39.330 --> 00:55:42.890 align:middle line:10%
we are discussing the
cosmos as much as we

00:55:42.890 --> 00:55:46.490 align:middle line:10%
discuss medicine or health.

00:55:46.490 --> 00:55:50.870 align:middle line:84%
It is the best way to discuss
the effect of the cosmos.

00:55:50.870 --> 00:55:57.620 align:middle line:84%
It is the only way I know
of that can change us

00:55:57.620 --> 00:56:01.360 align:middle line:84%
from the [INAUDIBLE]
prevailing today

00:56:01.360 --> 00:56:06.295 align:middle line:84%
at the government agencies, who
are worried about blackouts,

00:56:06.295 --> 00:56:10.046 align:middle line:84%
who are worried about
electronic engineering

00:56:10.046 --> 00:56:14.740 align:middle line:84%
and forget about the
effect upon ourselves.

00:56:14.740 --> 00:56:18.105 align:middle line:84%
Biologists don't
meet physicists,

00:56:18.105 --> 00:56:20.160 align:middle line:84%
and physicists don't
meet biologists.

00:56:20.160 --> 00:56:24.780 align:middle line:90%
Don't meet physician, and so on.

00:56:24.780 --> 00:56:33.000 align:middle line:84%
Sheldrake rightly speaks
about a live field,

00:56:33.000 --> 00:56:36.150 align:middle line:84%
and he calls it
morphogenetic field.

00:56:36.150 --> 00:56:40.410 align:middle line:84%
It's right, but I say
that the same field

00:56:40.410 --> 00:56:42.610 align:middle line:84%
that he calls
morphogenetic is what

00:56:42.610 --> 00:56:44.435 align:middle line:90%
physicists call electroweak.

00:56:44.435 --> 00:56:47.590 align:middle line:90%


00:56:47.590 --> 00:56:50.196 align:middle line:84%
FRANCINE BLAKE: Belief
is very limiting.

00:56:50.196 --> 00:56:52.710 align:middle line:84%
It limits you because
you begin to think

00:56:52.710 --> 00:56:57.450 align:middle line:84%
that what you believe in is
the only thing that can exist.

00:56:57.450 --> 00:56:59.880 align:middle line:90%
And that's not true.

00:56:59.880 --> 00:57:01.330 align:middle line:90%
So, belief is limiting.

00:57:01.330 --> 00:57:03.400 align:middle line:10%
Beyond belief is liberating.

00:57:03.400 --> 00:57:05.330 align:middle line:84%
But it's very
difficult to achieve

00:57:05.330 --> 00:57:07.500 align:middle line:90%
because we need security.

00:57:07.500 --> 00:57:10.500 align:middle line:84%
We need, like you
say, nuts and bolts.

00:57:10.500 --> 00:57:12.160 align:middle line:90%
We need to flesh it out.

00:57:12.160 --> 00:57:13.950 align:middle line:90%
We need to see something solid.

00:57:13.950 --> 00:57:16.400 align:middle line:84%
Beyond belief you are
actually in a position

00:57:16.400 --> 00:57:20.650 align:middle line:90%
where every possibility is open.

00:57:20.650 --> 00:57:24.000 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: How open are
we really for something

00:57:24.000 --> 00:57:27.310 align:middle line:90%
we don't believe in?

00:57:27.310 --> 00:57:29.590 align:middle line:84%
Yes, there are
several good examples

00:57:29.590 --> 00:57:32.240 align:middle line:84%
of events that we
simply ignore because

00:57:32.240 --> 00:57:34.230 align:middle line:90%
of our ingrained convictions.

00:57:34.230 --> 00:57:36.630 align:middle line:10%
Although we can perceive
them with all the senses

00:57:36.630 --> 00:57:40.460 align:middle line:10%
available to us today, even
measure and photograph them,

00:57:40.460 --> 00:57:42.810 align:middle line:10%
we refuse to admit that
they have any relevance

00:57:42.810 --> 00:57:44.675 align:middle line:10%
for our modern, clued-in life.

00:57:44.675 --> 00:57:46.635 align:middle line:90%


00:57:46.635 --> 00:57:48.135 align:middle line:84%
ILLOBRAND VON LUDWIGER
(THROUGH INTERPRETER):

00:57:48.135 --> 00:57:50.400 align:middle line:84%
It's the same with
consciousness research.

00:57:50.400 --> 00:57:52.890 align:middle line:84%
We suspect that it's
beyond our capacity,

00:57:52.890 --> 00:57:55.050 align:middle line:90%
so we won't even touch it.

00:57:55.050 --> 00:57:57.050 align:middle line:84%
You'll just earn yourself a
bad name among colleagues.

00:57:57.050 --> 00:58:04.510 align:middle line:90%


00:58:04.510 --> 00:58:08.956 align:middle line:90%
[BIRDS CALLING]

00:58:08.956 --> 00:58:35.140 align:middle line:90%


00:58:35.140 --> 00:58:37.740 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: After many
discussions such as these,

00:58:37.740 --> 00:58:41.060 align:middle line:84%
I came to the conclusion that
what we now call paranormal

00:58:41.060 --> 00:58:43.980 align:middle line:84%
is probably just the
tip of an iceberg.

00:58:43.980 --> 00:58:47.410 align:middle line:84%
Excerpts and messengers from
a world that we can't yet

00:58:47.410 --> 00:58:49.980 align:middle line:84%
perceive or understand
in the slightest.

00:58:49.980 --> 00:58:53.530 align:middle line:90%


00:58:53.530 --> 00:58:56.370 align:middle line:84%
One faction of
physicists is still busy

00:58:56.370 --> 00:58:59.310 align:middle line:84%
trying to bring the many
surprising and unexplained

00:58:59.310 --> 00:59:01.650 align:middle line:84%
characteristics of
elementary particles

00:59:01.650 --> 00:59:05.880 align:middle line:84%
into harmony with established
laws and standard models.

00:59:05.880 --> 00:59:08.010 align:middle line:84%
But some of their
colleagues have long since

00:59:08.010 --> 00:59:10.370 align:middle line:90%
left these limitations behind.

00:59:10.370 --> 00:59:13.600 align:middle line:10%
And in the process discovered
a world in which mathematics

00:59:13.600 --> 00:59:17.040 align:middle line:10%
and natural sciences
can indeed describe much

00:59:17.040 --> 00:59:20.460 align:middle line:10%
that has previously been
the exclusive prerogative

00:59:20.460 --> 00:59:22.780 align:middle line:10%
of religion and philosophy.

00:59:22.780 --> 00:59:26.250 align:middle line:84%
The only bitter pill, these
theories are so far away

00:59:26.250 --> 00:59:31.315 align:middle line:84%
from everything we've learned
thus far that now-- well,

00:59:31.315 --> 00:59:33.110 align:middle line:84%
before we attempt
this little excursion

00:59:33.110 --> 00:59:35.770 align:middle line:84%
into the world of
new physics, you

00:59:35.770 --> 00:59:38.862 align:middle line:84%
should try to free your
consciousness completely,

00:59:38.862 --> 00:59:41.780 align:middle line:84%
at least temporarily,
from everything

00:59:41.780 --> 00:59:45.250 align:middle line:90%
you've learned up until today.

00:59:45.250 --> 00:59:47.750 align:middle line:90%
[AUDIO SKIPS]

00:59:47.750 --> 00:59:52.235 align:middle line:90%
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

00:59:52.235 --> 01:00:25.037 align:middle line:90%


01:00:25.037 --> 01:00:27.860 align:middle line:10%
At the end of the
last century, someone

01:00:27.860 --> 01:00:33.020 align:middle line:10%
discovered a way of getting a
scientific grasp on eternity.

01:00:33.020 --> 01:00:36.260 align:middle line:10%
Physicist Burkhard
Heim developed a theory

01:00:36.260 --> 01:00:38.720 align:middle line:10%
that made it possible
to observe the world

01:00:38.720 --> 01:00:41.120 align:middle line:10%
holistically with
all its material

01:00:41.120 --> 01:00:45.240 align:middle line:10%
and non-material processes.

01:00:45.240 --> 01:00:48.340 align:middle line:84%
Postulating a
12-dimensional worldview,

01:00:48.340 --> 01:00:51.200 align:middle line:84%
he succeeded not
just philosophically,

01:00:51.200 --> 01:00:54.040 align:middle line:84%
but in a mathematically
calculable model

01:00:54.040 --> 01:00:56.690 align:middle line:84%
in uniting the two
aspects of life

01:00:56.690 --> 01:00:59.980 align:middle line:84%
that have been dogmatically
separated for centuries.

01:00:59.980 --> 01:01:01.770 align:middle line:90%
Matter and spirit.

01:01:01.770 --> 01:01:05.207 align:middle line:90%


01:01:05.207 --> 01:01:08.418 align:middle line:84%
But how can we imagine
a 12-dimensional world?

01:01:08.418 --> 01:01:12.250 align:middle line:90%


01:01:12.250 --> 01:01:14.580 align:middle line:84%
Let's say that our
life as we know it

01:01:14.580 --> 01:01:16.930 align:middle line:90%
all takes place in a computer.

01:01:16.930 --> 01:01:18.820 align:middle line:84%
We are all characters
in a virtual

01:01:18.820 --> 01:01:20.550 align:middle line:90%
three-dimensional reality.

01:01:20.550 --> 01:01:23.800 align:middle line:90%
A computer game, for example.

01:01:23.800 --> 01:01:26.940 align:middle line:84%
Everything around us--
colors, forms, objects--

01:01:26.940 --> 01:01:29.140 align:middle line:90%
is three dimensional.

01:01:29.140 --> 01:01:33.620 align:middle line:84%
All sequences and variations are
programed in a single time ray.

01:01:33.620 --> 01:01:35.540 align:middle line:84%
As long as we don't
interrupt the game,

01:01:35.540 --> 01:01:37.680 align:middle line:84%
time passes in
the linear fashion

01:01:37.680 --> 01:01:40.910 align:middle line:84%
we're familiar with
from our reality.

01:01:40.910 --> 01:01:43.350 align:middle line:84%
Einstein called this
virtual environment

01:01:43.350 --> 01:01:47.655 align:middle line:84%
with four dimensions, including
time, the space-time continuum.

01:01:47.655 --> 01:01:50.890 align:middle line:84%
It is the world of our
conscious experience.

01:01:50.890 --> 01:01:54.390 align:middle line:84%
Burkhard Heim combined these
dimensions in one space,

01:01:54.390 --> 01:01:57.095 align:middle line:90%
or Raum in German, called R4.

01:01:57.095 --> 01:01:59.890 align:middle line:90%


01:01:59.890 --> 01:02:02.600 align:middle line:84%
Remember, we're still talking
about a computer here.

01:02:02.600 --> 01:02:04.710 align:middle line:84%
So for anything
at all to happen,

01:02:04.710 --> 01:02:08.000 align:middle line:84%
we first need an operating
system, the prerequisite

01:02:08.000 --> 01:02:10.000 align:middle line:90%
for running any program.

01:02:10.000 --> 01:02:12.890 align:middle line:84%
In Heim's model, the equivalent
of the operating system

01:02:12.890 --> 01:02:15.480 align:middle line:84%
would be what he calls
structured space.

01:02:15.480 --> 01:02:18.800 align:middle line:84%
x5 and x6 is what he
calls the two dimensions

01:02:18.800 --> 01:02:21.130 align:middle line:90%
that comprise structured space.

01:02:21.130 --> 01:02:26.250 align:middle line:84%
Here, space and time already
cease to play a role.

01:02:26.250 --> 01:02:28.780 align:middle line:84%
Now everyone would agree that
without an operating system

01:02:28.780 --> 01:02:30.660 align:middle line:90%
the computer would be worthless.

01:02:30.660 --> 01:02:32.580 align:middle line:84%
We wouldn't be able
to play our game.

01:02:32.580 --> 01:02:37.560 align:middle line:84%
In other words, to
live our virtual world.

01:02:37.560 --> 01:02:41.160 align:middle line:84%
For that, the computer needs
additional data, a program

01:02:41.160 --> 01:02:44.050 align:middle line:84%
itself, as well as
numerous files in which

01:02:44.050 --> 01:02:47.380 align:middle line:84%
the visual appearance and
the laws of our virtual world

01:02:47.380 --> 01:02:49.050 align:middle line:90%
are preassigned and configured.

01:02:49.050 --> 01:02:53.030 align:middle line:90%


01:02:53.030 --> 01:02:55.140 align:middle line:10%
All this information
can be accessed

01:02:55.140 --> 01:02:58.900 align:middle line:10%
at anytime in the operating
system's root directories.

01:02:58.900 --> 01:03:02.490 align:middle line:10%
In Heim's model, these are the
information spaces, comprised

01:03:02.490 --> 01:03:04.390 align:middle line:10%
of the dimensions x7 and x8.

01:03:04.390 --> 01:03:07.220 align:middle line:90%


01:03:07.220 --> 01:03:12.120 align:middle line:84%
And finally, the itself has
to be located somewhere, too.

01:03:12.120 --> 01:03:15.750 align:middle line:84%
It accounts for
dimensions x9 to x12.

01:03:15.750 --> 01:03:20.130 align:middle line:84%
In our model, this space
has designation g4.

01:03:20.130 --> 01:03:24.930 align:middle line:84%
It is the realm of the
creator, the omnipresent higher

01:03:24.930 --> 01:03:29.060 align:middle line:84%
consciousness, the
source of mystery,

01:03:29.060 --> 01:03:33.730 align:middle line:84%
and the fundamental essence
behind man's search for meaning

01:03:33.730 --> 01:03:35.120 align:middle line:90%
and purpose in this world.

01:03:35.120 --> 01:03:37.670 align:middle line:90%


01:03:37.670 --> 01:03:39.800 align:middle line:90%
Take evolution.

